oons of fish sauce, 2 tablespoons of brown sugar, 2 tablespoons of tamarind paste, (peanut butter) 3) add vegetables, boil, then add crushed peanuts</h3>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n',1,'any','editor','true','false','wysiwyg','2014-11-09 03:08:47','2014-11-09 03:08:47'),(257,'wido_recipes','<p>Recipes</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Nasi Goreng</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1) 1 cup of white rice with 2 cups of water... &nbsp;cool down when done</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2) omelet from 3 eggs</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3) glaze onions/leeks/peppers ...5min</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>4) add chicken, later add shrimp &nbsp;...5min</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>5) add omelet, (cilantro), 3 tablespoons of ketjap</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- white rice</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- 3 eggs</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- 1/2 pound shrimp</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- 1/2 pound chicken</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- 1 leek</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- 2 spring onions</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- 2 peppers</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- (cilantro)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- ketjap</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- coriander</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Pad Thai</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- Annie Chung&#39;s pad Thai noodles</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- peanuts</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- (shrimp, tofu)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- lime</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- 2 spring onions</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- cilantro</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- soy sauce</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- fish sauce</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- brown sugar</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1) cook noodles</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2) sauce of 2 tablespoons of soy sauce, 2 tbsp of fish sauce, 2 tbsp of brown sugar, lime juice</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3) crush peanuts, chop onions, cilantro</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>4) scramble eggs, add sauce, then add noodles, (shrimp, tofu)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>5) add peanuts/onions/cilantro</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Masaman Curry</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- coconut milk</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- red curry sauce</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- peanuts</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- (peanut butter)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- small potatoes</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- carrots</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- other: leeks, sprouts...</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- fish sauce</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- tamarind paste</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- brown sugar</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1) combine 1 can coconut milk, equal red curry sauce</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2) add 3 tablespoons of fish sauce, 2 tablespoons of brown sugar, 2 tablespoons of tamarind paste, (peanut butter)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3) add vegetables, boil, then add crushed peanuts</p>\r\n',1,'any','editor','true','false','wysiwyg','2014-11-09 03:09:15','2014-11-09 03:09:15'),(258,'wido_genealogy','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>I have been working on a family tree. So far I have collected over 2000 people, and I\'ve been able to follow several lines back into the 1500\'s. I have also found relatives in California that I did not know existed, and I\'ve been able to connect to distant relatives all over the world who I had only heard about. I am planning to put this tree online (with some obfuscation for living relatives), but it\'s a bit of a job.</p>\r\n<p>One of the <a href=\"/files/menhardt/chronik_files/index.htm\">sources</a> is a family history for the Menhardt\'s, which my aunt Freia put together.</p>\r\n<p>Another is <a href=\"http://www.vieser.de/geneal/e/index.html\">this site</a> which was created by a distant relative on my father\'s mother\'s side.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',1,'any','editor','true','false','wysiwyg','2014-11-09 03:09:42','2014-11-09 03:09:42'),(259,'wido_genealogy_left','<%= include wido_left %>',1,'any','editor','true','false','wysiwyg','2014-11-09 03:10:01','2014-11-09 03:10:01'),(260,'wido_recipes_left','<%= include wido_left %>',1,'any','editor','true','false','wysiwyg','2014-11-09 03:10:15','2014-11-09 03:10:15');
